&ldquo;The players realise they&rsquo;re playing for a special manager. He protects the players, I think he takes a lot of pressure away. He&rsquo;s almost the figurehead. A lot of football clubs around Europe, they have maybe a player who&rsquo;s maybe the figurehead, like Messi maybe for Barcelona.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;At Liverpool it&rsquo;s more Jurgen is the figurehead. So, the players know to be successful, the best chance of success, they need to go with the manager and follow him. And I think he shows them the same amount of love and respect back.&rdquo;

🗣J&uuml;rgen Klopp:<br />
<br />
&ldquo;If I am trying to make signings I don&rsquo;t have to convince players anymore and tell them what Liverpool is. That is obvious.&rdquo;

